[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Wrestler Kaori Icho makes history with fourth straight gold

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Japanese wrestler Kaori Icho has become the first woman to win individual gold medals at four consecutive Olympics.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
The 32-year-old beat Russia's Valeria Koblova to win the -58kg freestyle wrestling division in Rio - as she has in every Games since Athens 2004.
Ten-time world champion Icho, whose 13-year undefeated record was ended in January, trailed with five seconds remaining but snatched victory.
Tunisia's Marwa Amri and Sakshi Malik of India won bronze medals.
